31:53.083 --> 31:55.051
Hence the day job.

31:55.085 --> 31:57.398
Actually, Hong Kong is a society

31:57.432 --> 32:00.573
that really values
elitism and professionalism.

32:00.608 --> 32:03.059
- Right.
- But in a way that, um,

32:03.093 --> 32:05.337
we are seeing
even these standards

32:05.371 --> 32:07.132
are falling apart
within the system.

32:07.166 --> 32:09.582
But it's important
to be part of a system

32:09.617 --> 32:11.067
to make any changes at all.

32:11.101 --> 32:12.171
- Right.
- Because,

32:12.206 --> 32:13.269
if you just stay on the fringe,

32:13.276 --> 32:14.863
it's very hard to get people

32:14.898 --> 32:16.935
to listen to you.

32:21.491 --> 32:23.148
What do young people want
in Hong Kong?

32:23.182 --> 32:25.253
Are they different
than the generation before?

32:25.288 --> 32:27.669
Or are they ready
to think about stuff

32:27.704 --> 32:28.774
and get angry?

32:28.808 --> 32:29.982
I think that society itself

32:30.017 --> 32:32.088
is projecting
a really unhealthy image

32:32.122 --> 32:33.882
of what young people
should be like.

32:33.917 --> 32:35.712
Because there's always a model

32:35.746 --> 32:37.956
of what the successful life is,

32:37.990 --> 32:39.440
which is to get a house by 30,

32:39.474 --> 32:41.960
have a family,
that sort of thing.

32:41.994 --> 32:44.307
It's not like you can
actually change anything.

32:44.341 --> 32:46.274
It's quite
a pessimistic thing to say,

32:46.309 --> 32:48.345
but it's...
It's more about doing things

32:48.380 --> 32:50.554
