34:43.426 --> 34:45.152
I may be in the "Hey, you kids",

34:45.186 --> 34:47.223
get off my lawn"
phase of my life

34:47.257 --> 34:49.293
and hostile in principle
about changes

34:49.328 --> 34:52.228
to age-old customs
and traditions I love,

34:52.262 --> 34:54.574
but it turns out
that the new Hong Kong

34:54.609 --> 34:56.956
has its hopeful aspects.

34:56.991 --> 34:58.441
Oh, yes.
This is bread and dip.

34:58.475 --> 35:00.236
This is sourdough, chicken fat,

35:00.270 --> 35:02.030
chicken stock, egg waffle.

35:02.065 --> 35:04.930
And this is
a Taiwanese bottarga.

35:04.964 --> 35:06.863
So just use your hands.
Wow.

35:06.897 --> 35:10.142
I am immediately happy.

35:10.177 --> 35:11.971
Chef-owner May Chow

35:12.006 --> 35:15.043
is the creative force
behind Happy Paradise,

35:15.078 --> 35:16.424
a restaurant and bar

35:16.459 --> 35:18.254
serving traditional
Cantonese dishes

35:18.288 --> 35:21.015
made with modern
cooking techniques.

35:21.049 --> 35:22.775
Joining us are Jenny Suen

35:22.810 --> 35:26.434
and feng shui master
Thierry Chow.

35:26.469 --> 35:28.126
Oh, my God, this food is great.

35:28.160 --> 35:29.610
How long have you been open?

35:29.644 --> 35:30.611
Seven months, only.

35:30.645 --> 35:32.268
Wait a minute.
Only seven months?

35:32.302 --> 35:33.993
- Yeah, yeah.
- So this is your new baby.

35:34.028 --> 35:35.333
It was a little bit
more reflection

35:35.340 --> 35:37.376
about being Chinese.
Like, how do I be modern

35:37.411 --> 35:39.620
but not lose the soul of it?

35:39.654 --> 35:40.897
Now, how important...

35:40.931 --> 35:43.555
And I should be asking...
I should be asking you this...

35:43.589 --> 35:46.213
Feng shui is something
I know nothing about.

35:46.247 --> 35:47.904
When you moved into the space,

35:47.938 --> 35:49.975
did you consult?

35:50.009 --> 35:51.839
- She's my friend, yeah.
- I was guessing.

35:51.873 --> 35:53.185
She's my friend.

35:53.220 --> 35:55.187
Feng shui is just
the environment

35:55.222 --> 35:57.569
and the relationship
between the environment

35:57.603 --> 35:58.811
and the people.

35:58.846 --> 36:00.330
When you're in a restaurant,

36:00.365 --> 36:03.333
when you're eating the food,
the space matters.

36:03.368 --> 36:04.714
It...

36:04.748 --> 36:07.199
It changes the way
you taste the food.

36:12.204 --> 36:14.068
So when you look at this space,

36:14.102 --> 36:17.313
what are you looking for
and what do you do?

36:17.347 --> 36:19.038
There's a couple things.

36:19.073 --> 36:21.317
So number one is,
I use a compass.

36:21.351 --> 36:24.354
So we're northeast, southwest.

36:24.389 --> 36:26.322
So from there,
we have a formula,

36:26.356 --> 36:29.221
and then that will tell us
where the best chi is.

36:29.256 --> 36:31.050
- What is chi?
- The energy

36:31.085 --> 36:34.675
that are given off
by the universe.

36:36.263 --> 36:38.851
So I look around,
and I see the colors

36:38.886 --> 36:41.751
of the decorations
and how the furnitures are.

36:41.785 --> 36:45.927
And then I can say, "Okay,
are these good placements?"

36:45.962 --> 36:48.240
♪

36:48.275 --> 36:50.242
It's all about
the flow of energy,

36:50.277 --> 36:52.106
where... where you're looking at,

36:52.140 --> 36:53.625
where the light comes from.

36:53.659 --> 36:55.627
Which is so...
Wait a minute.

36:55.661 --> 36:56.593
But a lot of what...

36:56.628 --> 36:58.043
A lot of what you've been saying

36:58.077 --> 36:59.527
in fact reminds me

36:59.562 --> 37:02.392
of a certain cinematographer
right now.

37:02.427 --> 37:04.256
Exactly.

37:04.291 --> 37:06.362
I wouldn't know.

37:06.396 --> 37:08.709
Positive energy
harnessed appropriately,

37:08.743 --> 37:10.573
one can turn
one's full attention

37:10.607 --> 37:11.781
to the food.

37:11.815 --> 37:14.128
Sautéed prawns with pomelo pith,

37:14.162 --> 37:16.406
fried shrimp roe, and prawn oil.

37:16.441 --> 37:19.409
Those are dishes that I feel
even Hong Kong people

37:19.444 --> 37:21.239
don't do it so much anymore,

37:21.273 --> 37:23.275
because it's such
an old-fashioned dish.

37:23.310 --> 37:24.794
So we want to make it
cool again.

37:24.828 --> 37:27.279
Tea smoked pigeon,
served medium-rare,

37:27.314 --> 37:29.488
sea salt on the side.

37:29.523 --> 37:31.145
A Hakka-style chicken,

37:31.179 --> 37:32.733
poached in Shaoxing wine

37:32.767 --> 37:34.769
with oyster mushroom fried rice

37:34.804 --> 37:35.839
and shitake broth.

37:35.874 --> 37:37.255
Again, this would feel

37:37.289 --> 37:39.740
like a very traditional
Cantonese dish.

37:39.774 --> 37:41.293
But it's not, because it doesn't

37:41.328 --> 37:44.400
really exist in its form
and combination.

37:44.434 --> 37:46.816
Pig brain
with burnt pear vinaigrette.

37:46.850 --> 37:48.852
All of it truly,

37:48.887 --> 37:51.269
stunningly delicious.

37:51.303 --> 37:52.684
There's something that I think

37:52.718 --> 37:54.582
binds all of us together,
which is,

37:54.617 --> 37:58.345
we're trying to reinterpret
Hong Kong culture

37:58.379 --> 38:00.933
in a way that makes sense to us.

38:00.968 --> 38:02.590
I think as we're getting older,

38:02.625 --> 38:05.697
we start to actually enjoy
our own culture.

38:05.731 --> 38:08.424
Think that's why you do that
movie about "The White Girl."

38:08.458 --> 38:10.149
Or she does, you know,
her feng shui.

38:10.184 --> 38:11.661
Because you want
to create something new...

38:11.668 --> 38:13.774
- Yeah.
- That represents the city

38:13.808 --> 38:15.638
as it is today.

38:15.672 --> 38:16.172
♪

38:26.234 --> 38:26.734
♪

38:38.557 --> 38:41.629
Okay, this is my
prawn grove noodle.

38:41.664 --> 38:43.321
Do you see how...
This is the part I...

38:43.355 --> 38:46.496
Wanna try it?
Yes, please.

38:46.531 --> 38:49.568
- What do you think?
- I love this.

38:49.603 --> 38:52.468
Douglas Young is the founder
and creative force

38:52.502 --> 38:55.471
behind the Hong Kong
lifestyle brand G.O.D.

38:55.505 --> 38:56.989
Okay, this is a classic.

38:57.024 --> 38:58.991
So it's the same stuff,
but without the prawn.

38:59.026 --> 39:00.648
I'm told that, what, two,

39:00.683 --> 39:03.202
maybe three people left
in all of Hong Kong

39:03.237 --> 39:05.550
are making bamboo noodles
the old-school way.

39:05.584 --> 39:06.854
- That's right.
- I mean, I've seen this

39:06.861 --> 39:08.346
process once before,
it's incredible.

39:11.383 --> 39:13.903
♪

39:13.937 --> 39:16.526
Lao Soong Kee is run
by the third generation

39:16.561 --> 39:18.079
of a family who still prepare

39:18.114 --> 39:20.358
their wontons from scratch...

39:20.392 --> 39:24.016
♪

39:26.743 --> 39:29.367
And make their noodles,
their bamboo noodles,

39:29.401 --> 39:31.610
the painfully labor-intensive,

39:31.645 --> 39:34.372
time-consuming, old-school way.

39:34.406 --> 39:34.906
♪

39:38.997 --> 39:41.793
One of the last operations
in Hong Kong

39:41.827 --> 39:43.933
to do this.

39:43.967 --> 39:44.467
♪

40:14.515 --> 40:17.242
It is one of many things
in this city

40:17.276 --> 40:20.314
that are under pressure
or disappearing.

40:20.348 --> 40:23.179
A lot of traditional crafts,

40:23.213 --> 40:24.456
buildings...
Yep.

40:24.491 --> 40:27.252
Are, without remorse
or sentiment,

40:27.286 --> 40:28.805
being bulldozed away.

40:28.840 --> 40:30.490
Well, that's the story
of Hong Kong, you know?

40:30.497 --> 40:31.801
Hong Kong is always
going through change,

40:31.808 --> 40:33.258
and nothing's precious,
it's as if...

40:33.292 --> 40:34.811
As if, you know,
if something's old,

40:34.846 --> 40:36.813
it's, like, torn down,
thrown away,

40:36.848 --> 40:39.126
destroyed.
That's Hong Kong.

40:42.509 --> 40:45.615
♪

40:45.650 --> 40:48.273
When I was a kid,
all the shopping

40:48.307 --> 40:49.757
used to be done on the street.

40:49.792 --> 40:52.933
There did not
used to be shopping malls.

40:52.967 --> 40:55.383
I miss the buildings
three stories high,

40:55.418 --> 40:58.801
instead of like glass facades.

40:58.835 --> 41:00.768
And actually, I think also

41:00.803 --> 41:02.390
in the way people dress,
as well.

41:02.425 --> 41:03.875
'Cause the people around here,

41:03.909 --> 41:07.119
they dress
in this kind of strange mix.

41:07.154 --> 41:09.467
I mean, even the look
of Chinese characters,

41:09.501 --> 41:10.985
to me, is very interesting.

41:11.020 --> 41:12.608
But it's disappearing
because, actually,

41:12.642 --> 41:14.368
mainland China
is trying to get rid

41:14.402 --> 41:16.612
of our Hong Kong
style of writing.

41:16.646 --> 41:18.476
We'll lose that as well.

41:18.510 --> 41:20.236
♪

41:20.270 --> 41:21.720
Those are beautiful to me.

41:21.755 --> 41:23.722
The things that
continually fascinating...

41:23.757 --> 41:24.999
- Yeah.
- Fascinate me about...

41:25.034 --> 41:26.414
That's what the city is about.

41:26.449 --> 41:27.726
But those are disappearing.

41:27.761 --> 41:29.314
Those are disappearing
because I think

41:29.348 --> 41:30.826
the government wants
to present an image

41:30.833 --> 41:33.249
that is like modern and Western.

41:33.283 --> 41:35.147
And so we've got
to clean ourselves

41:35.182 --> 41:36.804
of these sort of messy...

41:36.839 --> 41:38.426
- Yeah.
- Street people.

41:38.461 --> 41:39.731
And I think that's...
I hate that.

41:39.738 --> 41:41.637
Yeah, but I think actually

41:41.671 --> 41:44.053
our generation,
the new generation,

41:44.087 --> 41:46.987
is beginning to appreciate
what we have,

41:47.021 --> 41:50.093
because we grew up
in a wealthy period,

41:50.128 --> 41:52.820
and we had happy
childhood memories.

41:52.855 --> 41:54.408
So we wanted to preserve that.

41:54.442 --> 41:56.341
I really see it happening
in Hong Kong.

41:56.375 --> 41:58.170
Finally.

